Sharing The Love of The Game.

@nfl  @vikings safety @cambeezy_24 training the @wolvesfootballphilippines at the Alonte Sports Arena in the Philippines.

Last sunday, Cam shared his knowledge of the game to one of the Football communities in the Philippines. He focused on the fundamentals that will help build a strong foundation in Football.

His mission is to help outreach programs around the world especially his homeland the Philppines. He uses his platform in Football as a means to help the communities in need. He also wants to spread the sport globally, always eager to share his talents whenever possible.

Special thanks to @kingdags for making this possible. Thank you once again Cam for your time, the football community in the Philippines will forever be grateful.

March 4, 2023: Hope For Baybay, Leyte PART II

The sequel! @bynumfaithfoundation and @newlifecommunitycare will be returning to Baybay, Leyte as a follow up to our Outreach we put on last year. We will be bringing love, joy, and relief to the same families who are still evacuated due to last year’s destruction from the typhoons. More than just a one time operation 💙 Please join us in praying for this outreach! 

LINK IS IN MY BIO if you feel led to donate to support our cause 🙏🏾

To all of the beautiful families in Baybay, Leyte: I can’t wait to see you guys again for the sequel 🎬🇵🇭💙

March 4, 2023. Hope For Baybay, Leyte PART 2 🇵🇭

Two days after our wedding. No better honeymoon than to start our new life together serving others for the glory of Jesus. This time around was different. Coming back, seeing the same faces from last year, and witnessing the growth and progress in the families’ lives, my own life was changed. For me, simply giving resources is never enough. How can we do more? My goal every time we serve is to give the kids the best day of their life. A day to know that they are seen. A day to know that they are being prayed for by people all across the world. A day to see that God is a great provider. A day to see that their life is a movie. 

Without @newlifecommunitycare and @bynumfaithfoundation none of these visions would have been able to come to life. Thank you to all of our sponsors, people that donated, spread the word, and prayed for our work in the Philippines. Thank you to my people that traveled across the world to be here for this day. We thank you all in advance for the continued support for what is COMING SOON! LINK IN BIO 🙏🏾🎬🇵🇭

CampBeezy Volume 1: Movie In Manila 🎬🇵🇭🏈

Only by God’s grace, look where this game has taken me. 

History was made. We brought American Football to the Philippines. For the sport that changed my whole life, it would be selfish to not share it with the rest of the world. Welcome to the Philippines’ first Football camp ever. 

Thank you to all of the campers who came to learn and compete! So many people came together to make this movie happen and I could not thank you guys enough. All glory to Jesus! The football community in the Philippines will keep growing and we will need all of you to keep making these movies! #CampBeezy Volume 2 is already cookin 👀

It’s up to us to keep football growing. Where is football going to take you? 🎬🇵🇭

June 24-25, 2023: #CampBeezy Volume 1: Movie In Manila Final Video 🎬🇵🇭🏈

The month of October is Filipino American History month. Every week of this month, I will be sharing my favorite memories living in the Philippines from 2023, starting with CampBeezy! This is the start of us growing American Football in the Philippines 🇵🇭

July 1, 2023: Hope For Baybay, Leyte PART 3 🇵🇭

Baybay, Leyte will always have a special place in our hearts. In one year, this was our 3rd outreach to bless this specific community after a big typhoon destroyed everything that they had. They have now become our family. With @bynumfaithfoundation and @newlifecommunitycare we are blessed and grateful to be apart of their testimony. Listen to their testimony and see how God has worked in all of our lives. Thank you everyone for your giving to make this possible. So much more work to be done and more lives to be changed in Jesus’ name! 🙏🏾🇵🇭🎬 #FilipinoAmericanHistoryMonth
